Project Reflection:

Platforms I Selected:

For my digital portfolio, I created and regularly update my profiles on three main platforms: GitHub, LinkedIn, and Kaggle.

Purpose of Each Platform:

I selected these platforms because each one highlights a different aspect of my abilities for future employers.
GitHub works as a record of my technical work. 
It shows that I can write code and manage projects using version control tools like Git.
LinkedIn represents my professional identity.
It allows me to showcase my academic background, build connections with professionals, and explore internship or job opportunities.
Kaggle serves as a learning and practice space. 
Through it, I can solve real-world data problems, participate in competitions, and strengthen my analytical and machine learning skills.

My Four-Year Plan:

Over the next  four years, I aim to remain active on these platforms to create a strong digital presence.
During the first two years, I will focus on consistently uploading my college assignments, lab work, and small personal projects on GitHub to maintain an active contribution record.
In my third year, I plan to start sharing my achievements, certifications, and major project updates on LinkedIn so that I can attract attention from recruiters before the internship season.
By the final year, I will concentrate more on Kaggle, working on advanced projects and improving my portfolio so that I can present a polished and high-quality showcase of my skills by the time I graduate.
